where is this shot?

01:55.716 --> 01:57.116
Huh, huh?
- Oh, shit.

01:57.118 --> 01:58.484
- Does this look
below the neck? Huh?

01:58.486 --> 02:00.419
- No it does not.
- No it does not.

02:00.421 --> 02:01.720
Freakin' face shot.

02:01.722 --> 02:02.721
You...20 bucks.

02:02.723 --> 02:04.389
- Me?
- Yeah, you.

02:04.391 --> 02:05.891
- Twenty Bucks!
- Absolutely.

02:05.893 --> 02:07.426
- You should have a sip
of the homemade.

02:07.428 --> 02:09.428
- Yeah.
- Twenty bucks.

02:09.430 --> 02:11.730
Yeah, okay, but that--
that was kinda' worth it.

02:11.732 --> 02:13.599
- Oh, wow.

02:15.436 --> 02:16.802
- You know,
people have lost eyes.

02:16.804 --> 02:18.737
- [laughs]
- Oh, kiss my ass.

02:18.739 --> 02:20.839
- Oh, come on, Sunkist!
- Ted, Ted, Ted!

02:20.841 --> 02:22.674
- Look at the bright side.
- Don't run away.

02:22.676 --> 02:25.277
I think we found your color.
Orange looks terrific on you!

02:25.279 --> 02:26.912
You could go to a rave
right now.

02:26.914 --> 02:29.915
[music]

02:35.289 --> 02:38.524
- ¶ Well I can't understand
what is wrong with the man ¶

02:38.526 --> 02:40.325
¶ Don't he know how
he's acting ¶

02:40.327 --> 02:42.227
¶ Was long ago banned ¶

02:42.229 --> 02:43.629
¶ Don't you think it's a shame ¶

02:43.631 --> 02:45.430
¶ Someone tell me his name ¶

02:45.432 --> 02:46.632
¶ If we let him continue ¶

02:46.634 --> 02:51.603
¶ It may get out of hand ¶

02:51.605 --> 02:54.806
¶ Well, look at him laughing
and carrying on ¶

02:54.808 --> 02:58.343
¶ Like a hydrogen manic
or an organic bomb ¶

02:58.345 --> 03:00.279
¶ He's alive like a child ¶

03:00.281 --> 03:01.713
¶ So terribly wild ¶

03:01.715 --> 03:03.348
¶ He has way too much freedom ¶

03:03.350 --> 03:07.920
¶ Of course he is wrong,
he's wrong, yeah ¶

03:07.922 --> 03:11.456
¶ 'Cause he was born on the road
in the month of July ¶

03:11.458 --> 03:14.493
¶ And he'll live on the road
'til he sees fit to die ¶

03:14.495 --> 03:16.195
¶ 'Cause he learned
from the road ¶

03:16.197 --> 03:17.796
¶ How humanity cries ¶

03:17.798 --> 03:20.265
¶ How society lies ¶

03:20.267 --> 03:22.901
¶ He sees with more
than his eyes ¶

03:24.405 --> 03:25.938
¶ Well, look at him runnin' ¶

03:25.940 --> 03:27.940
¶ Don't he know how to walk ¶

03:27.942 --> 03:29.474
¶ He's just too damned cunning ¶

03:29.476 --> 03:31.210
¶ You can tell by his talk ¶

03:31.212 --> 03:32.678
¶ You can tell he is rude ¶

03:32.680 --> 03:34.580
¶ Like a typical dude ¶

03:34.582 --> 03:35.914
¶ If you want my opinion ¶

03:35.916 --> 03:40.819
¶ He belongs under lock ¶

03:40.821 --> 03:44.656
¶ One look in his eyes
and you know he's unsound ¶

03:44.658 --> 03:47.526
¶ There's no way to faze him
'cause he's nobody's clown ¶

03:47.528 --> 03:50.462
¶ He's as deep as the sea
and he's equally free ¶

03:50.464 --> 03:52.531
¶ That's why I fear him
and hate him ¶

03:52.533 --> 03:57.302
¶ And wish he was down,
was down, yeah ¶

03:57.304 --> 04:00.572
¶ 'Cause whether riding
the rails out of Denver ¶

04:00.574 --> 04:03.942
¶ Or bumming his friends'
cigarettes ¶

04:03.944 --> 04:07.312
¶ He's asking them all
to remember ¶

04:07.314 --> 04:11.650
¶ Making sure that
they'll never forget ¶

04:11.652 --> 04:13.318
¶ So you're curious, friend ¶

04:13.320 --> 04:15.354
¶ 'Bout this man who I speak ¶

04:15.356 --> 04:18.624
¶ 'Cause he tears you and
scares you out of your sleep ¶

04:18.626 --> 04:21.893
¶ I'm sure you'll find,
if you open your mind ¶

04:21.895 --> 04:23.262
¶ That it's you and not he ¶

04:23.264 --> 04:27.899
¶ Who is really the freak ¶

04:27.901 --> 04:31.803
¶ Oh, relax for a moment
as you would for your hobby ¶

04:31.805 --> 04:34.873
¶ His beauty abounds
in his mind and his body ¶

04:34.875 --> 04:38.710
¶ Like a setting sun's hues,
or the dust on his shoes... ¶

04:40.314 --> 04:42.714
You can't do that!
You always do that!

04:46.287 --> 04:47.653
No, you nimrod!
It's poker!

04:47.655 --> 04:49.655
It's not whatever
you want it to be!

04:51.759 --> 04:54.359
- You could set your clock
by those two.

04:54.361 --> 04:55.994
- Here they go.

04:55.996 --> 04:57.562
- Junior, back me up!

04:57.564 --> 04:59.998
- That's it. I'm out.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.601
- Night, big daddy.
- Night, Junior.

05:04.838 --> 05:05.904
- [sighs]

05:07.608 --> 05:08.740
- Whoa!

05:10.577 --> 05:13.378
- I'm good!
- [both laughing]

05:16.617 --> 05:19.518
- Ah, I love this place.

05:19.520 --> 05:21.386
- It's the Brook.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.057
- Come on.
- All right.

05:25.059 --> 05:27.693
- Come on. You referee.
- Ah, nah. Here we go.

05:27.695 --> 05:29.094
- Come on. Do it.
- Boxing glove.

05:29.096 --> 05:32.097
[music]

06:11.105 --> 06:12.137
- Oh!

06:19.747 --> 06:21.146
Ah, shit.

06:21.148 --> 06:22.147
- You okay over there?

06:22.149 --> 06:23.648
- Oh yeah, babe.

06:26.587 --> 06:28.086
Oh, yeah.

06:30.791 --> 06:31.857
- Okay.

06:37.598 --> 06:39.931
Oh, hey Cody!

06:39.933 --> 06:41.633
Time for school.

06:44.605 --> 06:45.670
I'll get him.

06:46.840 --> 06:48.640
[upbeat music playing]

06:48.642 --> 06:51.009
- Hey, hey Dude, Come on.

06:51.011 --> 06:53.111
Come on, you gotta go.
- You like this song, dad?

06:53.113 --> 06:54.946
- Yeah, sure. Come on.

06:54.948 --> 06:57.182
- That's very unconvincing, dad.
It's a great song.

06:57.184 --> 06:58.850
- All right, ya' wanna' know
another great song?

06:58.852 --> 07:00.051
It's called "I didn't miss
the school bus."

07:00.053 --> 07:01.486
Let's go.

07:02.956 --> 07:04.489
Wait a minute, come here.

07:06.059 --> 07:07.826
- No, no, it's--

07:07.828 --> 07:08.994
don't make my hair like yours.

07:08.996 --> 07:10.562
- I'm not. It's sticking up.

07:10.564 --> 07:12.831
You know what,
it's-it's my hair.

07:15.569 --> 07:16.835
- Okay?
- Yep.

07:18.605 --> 07:20.572
Oh, could you turn that off?

07:20.574 --> 07:24.443
¶ - ¶

07:24.445 --> 07:25.444
[music stops]

07:30.050 --> 07:31.216
- Remember dad,
I need twenty bucks

07:31.218 --> 07:33.051
for the field trip.
- Wha...

07:33.053 --> 07:35.520
Oh, right.

07:35.522 --> 07:38.056
Twenty. Okay.

07:38.058 --> 07:40.058
Okay.
- Thanks, dad!

07:40.060 --> 07:42.127
- Wrong daughter.
- What?

07:42.129 --> 07:44.196
- Dad, I need the money!
- You?

07:44.198 --> 07:46.865
Yeah, well that's--
hey, hey, hey, hey.

07:46.867 --> 07:48.533
- No.
- Really?

07:48.535 --> 07:50.235
- It's only fair, dad.

07:50.237 --> 07:52.671
- Dani, bring me the change.

07:52.673 --> 07:53.805
- There's no change
on a field trip.

07:53.807 --> 07:55.106
- Bye, mom!
- Bye!

07:55.108 --> 07:56.875
- Hey, hey, hey,
how about a kiss for dad?

07:56.877 --> 07:58.210
- Give your father a kiss,

07:58.212 --> 07:59.945
it's the only one
he's getting all day.

07:59.947 --> 08:01.546
- Bye, daddy. Bye, mom!
- Bye, bye.

08:01.548 --> 08:03.815
- Bye!
- Bye, girls.

08:03.817 --> 08:05.050
Wait, what?

08:05.052 --> 08:06.651
Do you have to give me
a hard time for?

08:06.653 --> 08:08.086
- Unbelievable.
- What?

08:08.088 --> 08:10.622
[laughing]

08:10.624 --> 08:12.924
You, are gonna need
a time out

08:12.926 --> 08:13.959
- You're so...
- Yep. Time out, time out.

08:13.961 --> 08:15.093
- You're the naughty one.

08:23.737 --> 08:24.836
- That was loud.

08:28.275 --> 08:29.808
- Hey.

08:31.979 --> 08:33.512
- Are we tight?

08:34.581 --> 08:35.881
- No, Ted, we're married.

08:35.883 --> 08:38.049
We got a teenage son.
We're not tight.

08:38.051 --> 08:39.217
- 'Cause I thought
we were tight.

08:39.219 --> 08:40.652
I really did.

08:40.654 --> 08:42.087
- How old are you?

08:42.089 --> 08:43.822
- What? Oh, come on.

08:43.824 --> 08:46.758
It was just a little paintball
at the Brook.

08:46.760 --> 08:48.627
- I think you just
made my point.

08:50.664 --> 08:52.697
- Mare...

08:52.699 --> 08:53.798
Mare!

08:59.006 --> 09:01.139
[music]

09:05.279 --> 09:06.978
- Hey, Junior.

09:06.980 --> 09:09.915
- Hilde!
Hey, where's your better half?

09:09.917 --> 09:11.249
- Junior!

09:11.251 --> 09:13.618
- Ted. Come here.

09:13.620 --> 09:15.654
- What's up?

09:15.656 --> 09:18.223
- Got a six pointer.

09:18.225 --> 09:19.624
- It's not deer season.

09:19.626 --> 09:21.293
- We'll talk.

09:21.295 --> 09:23.128
Order up!

09:23.130 --> 09:25.630
- Heard you got tagged
pretty good out there, Teddy.

09:25.632 --> 09:26.998
- Yeah, Ted.
I heard ya' took a header, huh?

09:27.000 --> 09:30.001
[laughter]

09:30.003 --> 09:31.636
- Hey, Frank.
How's it hangin'?

09:31.638 --> 09:32.871
- Hey, gravity, Hilde.

09:32.873 --> 09:36.107
Gravity always wins,
you know that.

09:36.109 --> 09:37.976
- I'm feelin' hash and eggs.
- Yeah?

09:37.978 --> 09:39.344
- Load 'em up, darlin'.

09:39.346 --> 09:41.613
- Do you look like
the only people in here?

09:43.283 --> 09:45.216
- ¶ Keep on ¶

09:45.218 --> 09:50.121
¶ Smilin' through the rain ¶

09:50.123 --> 09:54.659
¶ Laughin' at the pain ¶

09:54.661 --> 09:58.863
¶ Just rolling with changes ¶

09:58.865 --> 10:02.167
¶ 'Til the sun
comes out again ¶

10:02.169 --> 10:04.603
¶ Keep on smilin'... ¶

10:04.605 --> 10:05.870
- Hey, gorgeous.

10:05.872 --> 10:07.072
Any day.

10:09.009 --> 10:13.178
- ¶ Laughin' at the pain ¶

10:13.180 --> 10:16.615
¶ Just rolling
with the changes ¶

10:17.985 --> 10:20.018
¶ Singin' this refrain ¶

10:23.390 --> 10:26.391
[music]

10:36.236 --> 10:38.870
- Don't touch anything.
Watch your backpacks.

10:38.872 --> 10:41.873
[music]

10:47.781 --> 10:51.016
- Okay, kids, come on in.
Let's gather around this one.

10:51.018 --> 10:52.651
Come on over.

10:52.653 --> 10:54.252
I want to tell you
about this exhibit here,

10:54.254 --> 10:56.388
which is the Bernadine.

10:56.390 --> 10:58.223
Now aboard the Bernadine,

10:58.225 --> 11:00.725
these passengers left
the Port of New Orleans,

11:00.727 --> 11:02.761
headed for New York City.

11:02.763 --> 11:04.029
Now, these men and women,

11:04.031 --> 11:06.297
they had no idea
that they were doomed.

11:06.299 --> 11:08.767
But what makes this exhibit
so special

11:08.769 --> 11:11.102
is the phenomenal condition
of the historical pieces

11:11.104 --> 11:13.071
that belonged to these people,

11:13.073 --> 11:15.140
collected from this
one ship wreck.

11:15.142 --> 11:17.442
And together they create
a perfect snapshot

11:17.444 --> 11:19.210
of life in America,

11:19.212 --> 11:22.747
just before Civil War
would tear it apart.

11:22.749 --> 11:25.083
Now remember
what we learned last week;

11:25.085 --> 11:28.753
the Civil War started
in April of 1861.

11:28.755 --> 11:31.022
That was one year
after Abraham Lincoln

11:31.024 --> 11:32.290
was elected President.

11:32.292 --> 11:34.392
When seven states
in the deep south

11:34.394 --> 11:36.294
that supported
slavery seceded,

11:36.296 --> 11:37.896
forming a new nation.

11:37.898 --> 11:40.999
[flickers]

11:41.001 --> 11:42.467
- What the heck is that?

11:43.704 --> 11:46.071
- That's job security.

11:46.073 --> 11:48.106
- Ahh.

11:48.108 --> 11:49.874
- Are you really?
Still working on that?

11:49.876 --> 11:51.109
- Yeah.
- Come on.

11:51.111 --> 11:52.143
- All right.

11:54.014 --> 11:55.880
- [groaning]
- [laughing]

11:55.882 --> 11:58.116
How's that workin' out
for you?

11:58.118 --> 11:59.884
- I swear to God
I'm gonna hit you with this.

11:59.886 --> 12:02.253
[rattles]

12:02.255 --> 12:04.055
- [groaning]
- [laughs]

12:04.057 --> 12:05.290
- I just keep catching
Blue Gill,

12:05.292 --> 12:06.958
I wanna get
the Large Mouth Bass.

12:06.960 --> 12:08.326
- Well, what kind of fisherman
do you want to be?

12:08.328 --> 12:10.361
Because when I say fisherman,
it's "man",

12:10.363 --> 12:12.430
what kind of man
do you wanna be?

12:12.432 --> 12:14.432
You know?
- Yeah, I know.

12:14.434 --> 12:16.735
- Excuse me
ladies and gentlemen,

12:16.737 --> 12:19.003
the exhibit will be closing
in ten minutes.

12:19.005 --> 12:20.338
Ten minutes.

12:20.340 --> 12:22.941
Ten minutes from now.

12:24.177 --> 12:26.845
Enjoy.

12:26.847 --> 12:30.081
- The conditions,
the sediment on the sea floor,

12:30.083 --> 12:32.217
it's incredible, isn't it?

12:32.219 --> 12:33.918
Must be the pressure.

12:33.920 --> 12:34.919
- Hey guys,
I don't know if you heard,

12:34.921 --> 12:36.187
but we close in ten minutes.

12:36.189 --> 12:38.323
- This exhibit is wonderful.

12:38.325 --> 12:40.525
- Well, thank you.
Thank you.

12:40.527 --> 12:42.227
- We have ten minutes.
- Okay.

12:42.229 --> 12:43.528
- Well, actually nine.
- Let's go over here.

12:43.530 --> 12:46.397
- I'm sorry.
We have eight minutes.

12:46.399 --> 12:47.465
But...

12:53.306 --> 12:56.508
It's all worms, Wendall.

12:56.510 --> 12:58.476
No need for down-riggers,

12:58.478 --> 13:00.512
no need to troll, no lures,

13:00.514 --> 13:01.980
or the highly overrated chub.

13:01.982 --> 13:03.348
You don't have a chub, do you?
- No.

13:03.350 --> 13:04.349
- If you have a chub--
I will karate chop you.

13:04.351 --> 13:06.518
- No, I don't.
- Okay.

13:06.520 --> 13:09.220
It's worms.
Fish take the worm every time.

13:09.222 --> 13:10.321
What do you have
in your backyard?

13:10.323 --> 13:11.523
Go home,
look in your backyard.

13:11.525 --> 13:14.025
Under that little pool.
You have worms.

13:14.027 --> 13:16.528
You know what? You take off.
I'll lock it down.

13:16.530 --> 13:17.896
- I-I can go?

13:17.898 --> 13:19.864
- Yeah man, go.
- Ah thanks, Chip.

13:19.866 --> 13:21.099
- Yeah, sure, sure.

13:23.904 --> 13:24.969
Wendall.

13:26.339 --> 13:28.206
My locker,

13:28.208 --> 13:30.241
on top, July 02.

13:30.243 --> 13:31.876
Bongo bass.

13:33.079 --> 13:35.180
You take it home.

13:35.182 --> 13:37.081
- Wow, really?

13:42.355 --> 13:45.890
- Nah, it was an
all you can eat seafood bar.

13:45.892 --> 13:48.526
He sat down
and he ate shrimp cocktail

13:48.528 --> 13:50.395
for like an hour and a half.

13:50.397 --> 13:51.462
- Wait a minute.
You're telling me

13:51.464 --> 13:52.864
Junior got comp'd?

13:52.866 --> 13:55.166
- Yeah. Soup to nuts
at the Onondaga.

13:55.168 --> 13:56.968
- How does he do that?
- Well, you know Junior.

13:56.970 --> 13:59.103
He can hang with anybody.

14:04.144 --> 14:05.944
- Sir?

14:05.946 --> 14:07.979
The museum's closed now.

14:16.356 --> 14:18.223
- You can come back tomorrow.

14:20.861 --> 14:22.894
- The exit's
just right this way.

14:37.878 --> 14:40.178
How did Chip miss that?
[chuckles]

14:40.180 --> 14:42.046
- I don't know.

14:42.048 --> 14:45.049
- Yeah, right-right
this way, sir.

14:45.051 --> 14:46.050
Right this way.

14:46.052 --> 14:48.052
[light bulb clatters]

14:50.457 --> 14:52.657
- We have contact.

14:52.659 --> 14:54.392
Ah, hey, Twinkle Toes.

14:54.394 --> 14:56.060
Thanks for the spot?

14:56.062 --> 14:57.495
- What? You're fine.
Anyway, you're done.

14:57.497 --> 15:00.265
Come on. Get down.
It's time to go home.

15:00.267 --> 15:02.367
Let's go, let's go.

15:07.340 --> 15:09.340
[footsteps]

15:13.980 --> 15:15.079
- That's good, Hilde.

15:15.081 --> 15:17.115
Hey, I forgot my lunch box.

15:17.117 --> 15:18.182
- I got it!

15:18.184 --> 15:19.684
- All right, all right.

15:19.686 --> 15:22.921
- Did you see Chip's
new Mega Flashlight?

15:22.923 --> 15:24.589
He says it doubles as a club.

15:24.591 --> 15:26.057
- [snickers]

15:28.995 --> 15:30.028
Hilde...

15:32.299 --> 15:34.399
- How did he get back in here?

15:35.568 --> 15:37.101
- Call it in.

15:46.479 --> 15:47.946
- Oh, hey,
this is George Hildebrandt,

15:47.948 --> 15:49.347
over here at the, uh,
Museum of Art.

15:49.349 --> 15:51.316
Put me through
to the Campus Police, please.

16:00.493 --> 16:02.327
- Uh...

16:02.329 --> 16:03.361
sir?

16:06.232 --> 16:07.565
I'm sorry, Mister,
I thought we made it clear

16:07.567 --> 16:09.534
the exhibit was closed.

16:17.711 --> 16:18.977
Wait a minute...

16:26.519 --> 16:28.086
Hey.
Hey, you can't go down there!

16:28.088 --> 16:29.354
It's--come on, come on.
- I gotta go, gotta go.

16:29.356 --> 16:30.688
Thank you, send someone.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.457
Son of a...
- God damn it.

16:32.459 --> 16:33.691
- Where's he goin'?
Where's he goin'?

16:33.693 --> 16:35.259
- I have no idea.

16:42.102 --> 16:43.768
- That's a dead end.

16:47.540 --> 16:48.740
Okay.

16:53.179 --> 16:54.612
- Hey, mister.

16:56.416 --> 16:58.282
Listen...

16:58.284 --> 17:00.318
we don't want any trouble, okay?

17:04.224 --> 17:05.323
- What the...

17:08.495 --> 17:10.094
- [gasps]

17:10.096 --> 17:11.796
- Oh, sorry, kids.
Didn't mean to scare you.

17:11.798 --> 17:13.097
- Did you see a man
running out that door?

17:13.099 --> 17:14.699
- Running, running?
- No.

17:14.701 --> 17:15.633
- Where the hell did he go?
- Come on, he was just here.

17:15.635 --> 17:16.801
- What's happening?

