- We got a what?
- We got...

59:40.277 --> 59:41.343
Give me the mic.

59:41.345 --> 59:44.580
Base, we've got a 482.

59:44.582 --> 59:45.914
-<i> We got a what?</i>

59:45.916 --> 59:49.918
- We got an electrical incident.

59:49.920 --> 59:51.320
-<i> Who is this?</i>

59:51.322 --> 59:54.089
- This is Senior Sergeant
Ostrowski.

59:54.091 --> 59:55.824
-<i> What're you doin' there, Chip?</i>

59:55.826 --> 59:58.193
- I was--I was...

59:58.195 --> 1:00:00.095
I heard the call
and I was available.

1:00:00.097 --> 1:00:02.030
-<i> Uh, oh, okay.</i>

1:00:02.032 --> 1:00:04.266
- Okay,
so we are securing the area

1:00:04.268 --> 1:00:05.867
and we will advise.

1:00:05.869 --> 1:00:07.202
And we are out.

1:00:07.204 --> 1:00:09.304
[radio beeps]

1:00:09.306 --> 1:00:11.173
- Thanks, Chip.

1:00:11.175 --> 1:00:12.975
- Okay, so we're, we're gonna...

1:00:12.977 --> 1:00:15.777
Everyone, freeze!

1:00:15.779 --> 1:00:17.379
We are locking this area down!

1:00:17.381 --> 1:00:19.281
And we are gonna sweep
this area!

1:00:19.283 --> 1:00:20.349
- We are?

1:00:20.351 --> 1:00:22.317
- I am.

1:00:22.319 --> 1:00:23.385
I am.

1:00:27.157 --> 1:00:30.158
[music]

1:00:55.152 --> 1:00:56.218
- Hey, Cody, come on!

1:00:56.220 --> 1:00:58.153
Time for breakfast!

1:00:58.155 --> 1:00:59.688
- Oh, well, I already ate.

1:00:59.690 --> 1:01:01.957
- No, no, no, come on, let's go.

1:01:01.959 --> 1:01:03.358
Come on, let's go!

1:01:05.329 --> 1:01:07.329
- Jeez, dad, what's the rush?

1:01:10.334 --> 1:01:12.000
- Cody, grab your lunch,

1:01:12.002 --> 1:01:13.235
I'm gonna drive you to school
this morning.

1:01:13.237 --> 1:01:14.870
- Nate was gonna drive me.

1:01:14.872 --> 1:01:16.405
- Mm-mm-mm-mm,
with his learner's permit?

1:01:16.407 --> 1:01:17.806
That's not gonna happen.

1:01:17.808 --> 1:01:19.274
- Ah, come on.

1:01:19.276 --> 1:01:21.276
- Get you stuff.
You're gonna be late.

1:01:24.281 --> 1:01:26.048
- Worst day of my life.

1:01:26.050 --> 1:01:28.283
- And many more to come, dear.

1:01:31.288 --> 1:01:32.754
Ted?

1:01:32.756 --> 1:01:33.789
Would you come here
for a second?

1:01:33.791 --> 1:01:35.123
I gotta show you something.

1:01:45.269 --> 1:01:47.769
What is happening with him?

1:01:47.771 --> 1:01:49.404
- Oh, man, I don't know.

1:01:49.406 --> 1:01:53.208
He's just in that funny place
right now.

1:01:53.210 --> 1:01:55.110
- Yeah. I guess he is.

1:01:55.112 --> 1:01:56.044
I just...

1:01:56.046 --> 1:01:57.779
- He's 15.

1:01:57.781 --> 1:01:59.881
- Uh-hmm.

1:01:59.883 --> 1:02:02.851
How about us do you think?

1:02:02.853 --> 1:02:04.853
What place are we in?

1:02:09.226 --> 1:02:11.927
- We're just right here.

1:02:11.929 --> 1:02:13.328
Just you and me.

1:02:17.301 --> 1:02:19.868
- Oh, don't...

1:02:19.870 --> 1:02:21.269
- What?

1:02:21.271 --> 1:02:22.971
Ah, yeah.

1:02:22.973 --> 1:02:25.407
- You weren't
supposed to see that.

1:02:25.409 --> 1:02:26.475
- Wow.

1:02:27.911 --> 1:02:29.311
You showed up
with five friends.

1:02:29.313 --> 1:02:32.514
- [laughs] Hey, I showed.

1:02:32.516 --> 1:02:34.816
- And we were all so high.

1:02:34.818 --> 1:02:36.284
- And I looked over at you

1:02:36.286 --> 1:02:38.420
and you were wearing
that sweater that I knitted.

1:02:38.422 --> 1:02:40.155
And-and it wasn't perfect.

1:02:40.157 --> 1:02:42.057
- Which was kinda' perfect.

1:02:57.941 --> 1:02:59.841
- I gotta go.

1:02:59.843 --> 1:03:01.476
- Go.
- Okay.

1:03:01.478 --> 1:03:02.544
- Go.
- Okay.

1:03:04.448 --> 1:03:05.547
Cody!

1:03:18.896 --> 1:03:19.828
- Right there.

1:03:19.830 --> 1:03:21.029
- Oh, wow.

1:03:21.031 --> 1:03:21.963
- That's where he was.

1:03:21.965 --> 1:03:23.031
- Wow.

1:03:31.408 --> 1:03:33.108
- I'm lookin' at him and he's...

1:03:33.110 --> 1:03:34.342
I don't know what he's doing,
he looked back at me

1:03:34.344 --> 1:03:35.911
for a second.
- I know. I bet, I bet.

1:03:35.913 --> 1:03:37.312
- I don't know what to...

1:03:37.314 --> 1:03:40.315
[water gushing]

1:04:21.358 --> 1:04:23.291
- Y'all know where home is.

1:04:29.600 --> 1:04:32.367
Look, she would join me, she...

1:04:32.369 --> 1:04:34.536
she would look at me like...

1:04:34.538 --> 1:04:36.204
like I musta' done
somethin' wrong

1:04:36.206 --> 1:04:37.372
and then...

1:04:41.044 --> 1:04:43.111
then she smiles...

1:04:43.113 --> 1:04:44.179
Yeah.

1:04:45.415 --> 1:04:47.382
She'd smile...

1:04:51.388 --> 1:04:53.121
I know she'd do that.

1:04:57.327 --> 1:04:59.561
But I don't know where that is.

1:05:03.267 --> 1:05:04.966
How she gonna find me...

1:05:07.404 --> 1:05:09.104
if I ain't there?

1:05:10.107 --> 1:05:11.172
Huh?

1:05:15.612 --> 1:05:18.079
- Gil I-I don't know
how to help you.

1:05:24.688 --> 1:05:26.521
- I wants home.

1:05:39.469 --> 1:05:42.103
- Did you hear what he said,
Ted?

1:05:42.105 --> 1:05:43.471
He was talking about his wife.

1:05:43.473 --> 1:05:44.940
- I know, I know.

1:05:44.942 --> 1:05:46.274
It's-it's like he's aimlessly

1:05:46.276 --> 1:05:47.442
walking the earth. I...

1:05:47.444 --> 1:05:49.277
- Wait a minute.

1:05:49.279 --> 1:05:50.445
Wait.

1:05:50.447 --> 1:05:51.713
What if it's not aimless?

1:05:53.617 --> 1:05:55.317
Oh, man.

1:05:55.319 --> 1:05:57.118
- What?
- Oh man, Ted,

1:05:57.120 --> 1:05:59.454
what if he doesn't leave?

1:05:59.456 --> 1:06:01.156
What if Gil just stays
right here, right?

1:06:01.158 --> 1:06:04.059
- I mean, we just saw him
in the backyard, right?

1:06:04.061 --> 1:06:05.493
Where-where we gonna find him
next?

1:06:05.495 --> 1:06:07.462
Like, hanging out
in the kids' room?

1:06:10.300 --> 1:06:12.701
- No, no I don't want him
in the kid's room.

1:06:12.703 --> 1:06:14.469
- Ah man,
this is really happening.

1:06:14.471 --> 1:06:17.038
- All of it.
And I'm feelin' all this stuff

1:06:17.040 --> 1:06:19.341
that we can't really share
with anybody.

1:06:19.343 --> 1:06:20.742
I mean, it's incredible.

1:06:20.744 --> 1:06:22.677
And it makes me feel
like we're special,

1:06:22.679 --> 1:06:24.045
in some way, or crazy.

1:06:24.047 --> 1:06:25.180
But whatever it is,

1:06:25.182 --> 1:06:26.648
it's just you and me.

1:06:26.650 --> 1:06:28.583
And we don't even know why.

1:06:31.088 --> 1:06:32.153
Why?

1:06:34.157 --> 1:06:35.690
- He needs to go home.

1:06:41.198 --> 1:06:44.199
[car engine revving]

1:06:47.437 --> 1:06:48.703
- Are we just gonna take it?

1:06:48.705 --> 1:06:50.672
Like, we're gonna steal it?

1:06:50.674 --> 1:06:52.374
- No, we're gonna borrow it.

1:06:52.376 --> 1:06:55.510
The clerk said to have
the actual deed in hand.

1:06:55.512 --> 1:06:57.479
So, let's do that, right?
Let's give him that.

1:06:57.481 --> 1:07:00.782
- I don't think
he meant it literally.

1:07:00.784 --> 1:07:02.050
- Oh, shoot.

1:07:07.190 --> 1:07:08.356
- What're you doin'?

1:07:08.358 --> 1:07:09.290
- Look.

1:07:12.195 --> 1:07:13.528
- Who is that?

1:07:13.530 --> 1:07:14.796
- I can't tell.

1:07:16.199 --> 1:07:17.132
- Is that Chip?

1:07:17.134 --> 1:07:19.467
- Oh, shit.

1:07:19.469 --> 1:07:22.470
[car engine starts and revs]

1:07:42.059 --> 1:07:43.124
- Alright.

1:07:46.563 --> 1:07:47.829
- Oh, boy.

1:07:47.831 --> 1:07:49.230
You sure about this?

1:07:49.232 --> 1:07:50.298
- No.

1:07:51.635 --> 1:07:53.835
No, I am not.

1:08:06.817 --> 1:08:08.349
- Hey, Ted.

1:08:08.351 --> 1:08:09.584
What if we run into someone,

1:08:09.586 --> 1:08:11.119
or somebody sees us?

1:08:11.121 --> 1:08:13.421
- If they do, we're just fixing
the electrical.

1:08:13.423 --> 1:08:16.357
- I'm not sure needing an alibi
is a good thing.

1:08:17.527 --> 1:08:19.527
- Oh, look at that baby.

1:08:21.531 --> 1:08:24.199
- Hello! Get the...

1:08:24.201 --> 1:08:26.734
Don't touch him. You don't know
what kind of spider that is.

1:08:26.736 --> 1:08:29.737
[music]

1:08:32.876 --> 1:08:35.310
- Is it clear?

1:08:35.312 --> 1:08:37.245
- Yeah, yeah. Come on, come on.

1:08:37.247 --> 1:08:40.248
[music]

1:08:42.686 --> 1:08:44.886
- Really? Really?
- I know, I know.

1:08:44.888 --> 1:08:47.889
[music]

1:08:54.731 --> 1:08:56.264
- Come on.

1:08:56.266 --> 1:08:58.733
[music]

1:09:14.151 --> 1:09:15.283
- Ted.

1:09:15.285 --> 1:09:16.584
- What?

1:09:16.586 --> 1:09:17.719
- I can't make the guy out,

1:09:17.721 --> 1:09:19.687
but he's still standing there.

1:09:19.689 --> 1:09:21.723
- Well, still keep looking
at him, okay?

1:09:21.725 --> 1:09:23.591
- Okay. Hurry up.

1:10:09.506 --> 1:10:11.806
- Hilde.
- Yeah.

1:10:11.808 --> 1:10:13.675
- Come here. You gotta see this.

1:10:22.385 --> 1:10:24.986
Look. For Gil.

1:10:27.324 --> 1:10:29.224
- That's his land.

1:10:29.226 --> 1:10:30.291
- Yeah.

1:10:34.264 --> 1:10:36.497
Shh.

1:10:36.499 --> 1:10:38.566
Listen.

1:10:38.568 --> 1:10:40.935
Next time we do this,
make more noise.

1:10:40.937 --> 1:10:42.303
- I know.

1:10:50.814 --> 1:10:52.413
- I'm telling you,

1:10:52.415 --> 1:10:53.982
no one is gonna know
that that deed

1:10:53.984 --> 1:10:54.983
is not in that pouch.

1:10:54.985 --> 1:10:55.984
- Hey, hey, hey.
- What?

1:10:55.986 --> 1:10:57.518
- Did we leave our light on?

1:10:58.622 --> 1:10:59.887
- No.

1:11:09.633 --> 1:11:12.267
- I come back here tonight,
'cause I figure that if,

1:11:12.269 --> 1:11:13.534
you know...

1:11:14.971 --> 1:11:17.438
something could go wrong,
and it did,

1:11:17.440 --> 1:11:19.741
and maybe it could happen again,

1:11:19.743 --> 1:11:22.043
and I wanted to go
that extra mile.

1:11:22.045 --> 1:11:23.278
For the job.

1:11:23.280 --> 1:11:24.779
For the sake of making sure

1:11:24.781 --> 1:11:26.447
that everything
is gonna be all right.

1:11:26.449 --> 1:11:29.684
I mean, he may be out there...

1:11:29.686 --> 1:11:30.918
but he's not gonna be in here.

1:11:30.920 --> 1:11:32.687
No sirree, no Bob, no.

1:11:32.689 --> 1:11:35.323
Not on my watch.

1:11:35.325 --> 1:11:38.326
So, I post one of my guys
outside the front door.

1:11:39.396 --> 1:11:41.496
And guess what I saw.

1:11:41.498 --> 1:11:44.465
I saw our local heroes.

1:11:44.467 --> 1:11:45.900
Which makes me wonder.

1:11:48.305 --> 1:11:49.871
Did you get another call?

1:11:49.873 --> 1:11:52.707
Was there another
"electrical incident"

1:11:52.709 --> 1:11:54.542
and so they called you guys?

1:11:54.544 --> 1:11:56.611
- Chip--
- You guys are maintenance.

1:11:58.381 --> 1:12:00.848
You maintain things.
I'm supposed to be security,

1:12:00.850 --> 1:12:03.084
but apparently
I don't secure much of anything.

1:12:08.625 --> 1:12:11.359
I thought you guys
were taking it to 11...

1:12:13.096 --> 1:12:14.696
but really...

1:12:17.600 --> 1:12:19.967
all you were really doing
was taking.

1:12:19.969 --> 1:12:22.737
- Wait. Chip.

1:12:22.739 --> 1:12:26.741
It's just an old a deed,
to a piece of land,

1:12:26.743 --> 1:12:29.911
and we just need to borrow it
for a short time.

1:12:29.913 --> 1:12:32.547
That's it. And then we're gonna
put it back.

1:12:34.517 --> 1:12:36.718
- But what does it have
to do with you?

1:12:41.825 --> 1:12:44.592
You know what? Listen.

1:12:47.731 --> 1:12:49.731
I don't know what you guys
are gonna do with that thing,

1:12:49.733 --> 1:12:51.499
you know what,
I don't wanna know.

1:12:54.871 --> 1:12:57.438
But I'm gonna give you one day.

1:12:57.440 --> 1:12:59.507
That's it. 24 hours.

1:13:00.944 --> 1:13:03.878
And then you're gonna bring
it back to me.

1:13:03.880 --> 1:13:05.813
You're gonna give it to me.
- You got it.

1:13:05.815 --> 1:13:07.048
- Okay.

1:13:09.619 --> 1:13:11.586
- Me only, okay?

1:13:11.588 --> 1:13:12.987
- Yeah.
- Yep.

1:13:23.500 --> 1:13:26.934
[music]

1:13:58.635 --> 1:14:01.636
[vacuum whirring]

1:14:13.550 --> 1:14:16.651
- Oh. Hey, Sweetie.
- Hey.

1:14:16.653 --> 1:14:18.052
I can't believe
you slept there all night.

1:14:18.054 --> 1:14:19.987
I tried to wake you up.
- I know.

1:14:19.989 --> 1:14:21.489
- You didn't wake up.

1:14:21.491 --> 1:14:22.490
- Hi.
- You didn't wake up

1:14:22.492 --> 1:14:23.458
when the girls left.

1:14:23.460 --> 1:14:24.892
- Oh no, I know.

1:14:37.807 --> 1:14:39.207
Hey, Rach.
- Oh, God.

1:14:39.209 --> 1:14:41.809
I thought you were downstairs.
- Sorry, uh...

1:14:41.811 --> 1:14:43.978
I just, uh, need to take
those papers to work.

1:14:43.980 --> 1:14:46.681
Didn't want to forget 'em.
- What is this?

1:14:46.683 --> 1:14:48.049
- Uh, it's an old map.

1:14:48.051 --> 1:14:50.685
Um, can I have it?

1:14:50.687 --> 1:14:52.220
Don't, but, don't-don't-

1:14:52.222 --> 1:14:53.754
don't bend it like that, Rach.

1:14:53.756 --> 1:14:55.089
It's a hundred
and fifty years old.

1:14:55.091 --> 1:14:56.157
- What are you doing
with it then?

1:14:56.159 --> 1:14:57.625
- Just give it to me?

1:14:59.062 --> 1:15:00.628
Please.

1:15:07.737 --> 1:15:10.571
Okay. The man?

1:15:10.573 --> 1:15:12.540
That we were chasing
in the Museum that night?

1:15:12.542 --> 1:15:14.575
- Uh-huh.

1:15:14.577 --> 1:15:16.010
- That's him.

1:15:17.747 --> 1:15:19.981
- What's him? Who's him?
- The-the black guy.

1:15:19.983 --> 1:15:22.517
That everyone's looking for.
- But you just said

1:15:22.519 --> 1:15:24.252
it's a hundred
and fifty years old.

1:15:24.254 --> 1:15:25.786
- I know it's crazy.

1:15:25.788 --> 1:15:27.855
I just want to help him
get back home,

1:15:27.857 --> 1:15:29.957
and then I'll take it
back to the museum.

1:15:31.928 --> 1:15:33.728
- You took this from the museum?

1:15:33.730 --> 1:15:36.697
From the college where you work?

1:15:36.699 --> 1:15:39.066
Do you know what's gonna happen
when they find this missing?

1:15:39.068 --> 1:15:41.569
You'll lose your job.
- I'm not gonna lose my job.

1:15:41.571 --> 1:15:43.237
- You would put this family,
this place,

1:15:43.239 --> 1:15:45.873
everything we eek out
for a living at risk?

1:15:45.875 --> 1:15:47.875
- Nothing's gonna be at risk.

1:15:47.877 --> 1:15:49.544
- Really?

1:15:49.546 --> 1:15:50.811
You sure about that?

1:15:57.687 --> 1:15:59.020
- Ted?

1:16:01.624 --> 1:16:02.790
- Yeah?

1:16:04.227 --> 1:16:06.160
- Where's your girlfriend going
so early?

1:16:12.168 --> 1:16:14.101
- Uh...

1:16:14.103 --> 1:16:16.203
can you help me clean up
a little bit? I gotta...

1:16:16.205 --> 1:16:17.171
- Go.

1:16:18.575 --> 1:16:19.774
- Okay.

1:16:37.727 --> 1:16:39.293
What'd you have in mind
for that?

1:16:40.797 --> 1:16:42.363
- I was gonna put it back.

1:16:47.270 --> 1:16:48.836
- Okay.

1:16:56.379 --> 1:16:58.212
Did you tell Rachel?

1:17:01.117 --> 1:17:02.950
Ah, no.

1:17:04.320 --> 1:17:06.253
- Is it worth it, Ted?

1:17:08.257 --> 1:17:09.890
- Is it worth it?

1:17:13.062 --> 1:17:15.896
I don't know, Hilde,
but I'll tell you somethin'.

1:17:19.335 --> 1:17:21.902
If it doesn't work out,
or we don't find Gil

1:17:21.904 --> 1:17:24.071
or his land by tonight...

1:17:26.075 --> 1:17:28.676
we're gonna bring that back,
we're gonna give it to Chip,

1:17:28.678 --> 1:17:31.145
the exhibit reopens,
nobody's the wiser,

1:17:31.147 --> 1:17:32.980
and nobody...

1:17:32.982 --> 1:17:34.649
is gonna get hurt by it.

1:17:34.651 --> 1:17:37.251
- If we get caught,
we lose our jobs.

1:17:37.253 --> 1:17:40.855
- If we get caught,
we're goin' to jail. [laughs]

1:17:40.857 --> 1:17:42.323
- Oh, come on.
You think this is funny?

1:17:42.325 --> 1:17:45.159
- No. No, I...

1:17:45.161 --> 1:17:46.360
I don't.

1:17:47.664 --> 1:17:49.296
Hilde.

1:17:49.298 --> 1:17:51.732
I do not think that Chip
is gonna tell anybody.

1:17:51.734 --> 1:17:53.200
We're the closest thing
he has to friends.

1:17:53.202 --> 1:17:56.737
I know that sounds pathetic,
but it's true.

1:17:56.739 --> 1:17:58.806
We've got to do this.

1:17:59.809 --> 1:18:01.842
- Why?

1:18:01.844 --> 1:18:03.177
- I don't know.

1:18:05.948 --> 1:18:08.182
But when's the last time
you felt like this?

1:18:10.219 --> 1:18:12.119
- I just can't shake
this sense I have

1:18:12.121 --> 1:18:13.688
that he's here, right now.

1:18:13.690 --> 1:18:15.756
Not just because he's lost.

1:18:15.758 --> 1:18:17.458
- Yeah, but I really think
he is lost.

1:18:17.460 --> 1:18:20.227
- Yeah, but we ain't.

1:18:20.229 --> 1:18:22.830
Everything was fine, Ted.

1:18:22.832 --> 1:18:24.965
